2ï¸âƒ£ CÃ i thÆ° viá»‡n Deep Learning
pip install tensorflow


(TensorFlow bao gá»“m Keras â€“ dá»… dÃ¹ng)

3ï¸âƒ£ Dataset Ä‘Æ¡n giáº£n (Ä‘áº­u / rá»›t)
import numpy as np
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

X = np.array([
    [4, 4],
    [5, 5],
    [6, 6],
    [7, 7],
    [8, 8],
    [9, 9]
])

y = np.array([0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1])

4ï¸âƒ£ Chuáº©n hÃ³a dá»¯ liá»‡u (Báº®T BUá»˜C)
scaler = StandardScaler()
X = scaler.fit_transform(X)

5ï¸âƒ£ XÃ¢y Neural Network Ä‘áº§u tiÃªn
model = Sequential([
    Dense(8, activation="relu", input_shape=(2,)),
    Dense(4, activation="relu"),
    Dense(1, activation="sigmoid")
])


ðŸ‘‰ Giáº£i thÃ­ch:

2 input (math, english)

Hidden layers: 8 â†’ 4 neuron

Output: 1 (Ä‘áº­u / rá»›t)

6ï¸âƒ£ Compile model
model.compile(
    optimizer="adam",
    loss="binary_crossentropy",
    metrics=["accuracy"]
)

7ï¸âƒ£ Train AI
model.fit(X, y, epochs=100, verbose=0)


ðŸŽ‰ Báº¡n vá»«a train Deep Learning model

8ï¸âƒ£ Dá»± Ä‘oÃ¡n
new_student = scaler.transform([[6, 8]])
prob = model.predict(new_student)
print(prob)          # xÃ¡c suáº¥t
print(prob > 0.5)    # True = Ä‘áº­u
